headlines.description: Matt Ryan to Julio Jones failed again.
headlines.shortLinkText: Eagles stop Ryan to Jones again, beat Falcons 18-12
Browns don't lose, tie Steelers 21-21 in sloppy game

headlines.description: Andy Dalton rallied the Cincinnati Bengals with three scores in the final 19 minutes Sunday and Clayton Fejedelem scored on an 83-yard fumble return with 24 seconds to go, giving the Bengals a 34-23 victory at Indianapolis.
headlines.shortLinkText: Bengals rally late to spoil Luck's return with 34-23 win

headlines.description: Jakeem Grant scored on a tiebreaking 102-yard kickoff return with 14 minutes to go, and the Miami Dolphins overcame two weather delays to win the longest game since the 1970 NFL-AFL merger, beating the Tennessee Titans 27-20 Sunday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Dolphins overcome 2 lightning delays to beat Titans 27-20

headlines.description: Kirk Cousins passed for two touchdowns in his much-anticipated Minnesota debut, and the Vikings forced four turnovers to fuel a 24-16 victory over San Francisco on Sunday to stick 49ers quarterback Jimmy Garoppolo with his first loss in eight games as...
headlines.shortLinkText: Cousins, Vikings hold on for 24-16 victory vs. 49ers

events.name: Houston Texans at New England Patriots

headlines.description: Tom Brady threw for 277 yards and three touchdowns, hitting Rob Gronkowski for 123 yards and a score Sunday to lead the defending AFC champion New England Patriots to a 27-20 victory over the Houston Texans.
headlines.shortLinkText: Brady, Gronk open season with 27-20 win over Texans

events.name: Tampa Bay Buccaneers at New Orleans Saints

headlines.description: Ryan Fitzpatrick highlighted a 417-yard, four-touchdown performance with two scoring strikes of more than 50 yards, and the Tampa Bay Buccaneers stunned the New Orleans Saints 48-40 on Sunday.

events.name: Jacksonville Jaguars at New York Giants

headlines.description: Just like last season, the Jacksonville defense is carrying the team.
headlines.shortLinkText: Jack interception return leads Jags over Barkley, Giants

headlines.description: The Baltimore Ravens harassed and embarrassed Buffalo quarterback Nathan Peterman on a rainy Sunday afternoon and beat the rebuilding Bills 47-3.
headlines.shortLinkText: Ravens get defensive in 47-3 rout of inept Bills

events.name: Kansas City Chiefs at Los Angeles Chargers

headlines.description: Tyreek Hill scored three touchdowns, Patrick Mahomes passed for his first four NFL scores and the Kansas City Chiefs opened the season with a 38-28 victory over the Los Angeles Chargers on Sunday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Hill, Mahomes lead Chiefs to 38-28 victory over Chargers

headlines.description: Von Miller sacked Russell Wilson three times, forced two fumbles and recovered one in helping Case Keenum win his Denver debut Sunday when the Broncos held off the Seattle Seahawks 27-24.

Alex Smith carved up the Arizona defense for 255 yards and two touchdowns, Adrian Peterson rushed for 96 yards and a score and the Washington Redskins spoiled the Cardinals coaching debut of Steve Wilks with a dominant 24-6 victory on Sunday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Smith, Peterson led Redskins to 24-6 victory at Arizona

headlines.description: Cam Newton ran for 58 yards and a touchdown, and Carolina's defense turned in a dominating performance as the Panthers defeated the Dallas Cowboys 16-8 in the season opener Sunday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Newton, defense lead Panthers past Cowboys 16-8

events.name: Chicago Bears at Green Bay Packers

headlines.description: Aaron Rodgers threw three touchdown passes in the second half after returning from a knee injury, and the Green Bay Packers overcame a 20-point deficit for a thrilling 24-23 win over the Chicago Bears on Sunday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Rodgers returns from injury, Packers beat Bears 24-23

events.name: New York Jets at Detroit Lions

headlines.description: Sam Darnold made a stellar debut despite throwing a pick-6 on his first NFL pass and the New York Jets intercepted five passes while routing the Detroit Lions 48-17 in their season opener Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Darnold recovers from 1st-play pick-6, helps Jets rout Lions

events.name: Los Angeles Rams at Oakland Raiders

headlines.description: Jared Goff threw two touchdown passes, newcomer Marcus Peters returned an interception 50 yards for a touchdown and the Los Angeles Rams spoiled coach Jon Gruden's much-anticipated return to the Oakland sideline by beating the Raiders 33-13 on Monday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Rams spoil Gruden's return with 33-13 win over Raiders
